reasoning: Endodermal sinus tumors (yolk sac tumors) are the most common germ cell tumor of the ovary, typically affecting adolescents and young women. Ovarian germ cell tumors comprise ~3-5% of all ovarian cancers (incidence ~5 per 100k). Endodermal sinus tumors represent ~40% of these, giving ~0.3 per 100k. Based on cancer registry data and gynecologic oncology literature.
